OL,6,FThe Northern Ireland Office, in a
OL,7,Fstatement said: "The Belfast (Good
OL,8,FFriday) Agreement is clear that any
OL,9,Fchange to the constitutional position
OL,10,Fof Northern Ireland would require the
OL,11,Fconsent of a majority of its people.
OL,12,F"In accordance with the Principle of
OL,13,FConsent, Northern Ireland will remain
OL,14,Fpart of the UK for as long as its
OL,15,Fpeople wish for it to be. "We are
OL,16,Fabsolutely clear that there is no
OL,17,Fbasis to suggest that a majority of
OL,18,Fpeople in Northern Ireland wish to
OL,19,Fseparate from the United Kingdom."
